[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      380[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ### Dispatch Decision Audit Trail
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      381[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      382[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Every dispatch decision must be logged as an immutable audit record. In EMS, dispatch records are legal documents. They may be subpoenaed in malpractice cases, reviewed by medical directors for quality assurance, or examined by regulatory bodies during accreditation audits. The audit trail is not optional.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      383[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      384[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **What gets logged (full decision payload):**
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      385[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      386[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Field | Description |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      387[0m:[38;5;10m[49m |-------|-------------|
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      388[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | `call_id` | Unique identifier from the CAD system |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      389[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | `call_priority` | Priority level at time of dispatch |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      390[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | `call_location` | GPS coordinates of the incident |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      391[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | `nature_code` | Dispatch nature code (chest pain, trauma, etc.) |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      392[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | `all_candidate_scores` | Every unit evaluated, with individual score components (travel time, coverage impact, fatigue, workload) |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      393[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | `fleet_state_snapshot` | Positions and statuses of all units at decision time |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      394[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | `travel_times_used` | The travel time values that informed scoring (and their source: cache hit vs. Location Service call) |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      395[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | `assigned_unit_id` | Which unit the optimizer recommended |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      396[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | `dispatcher_action` | Accept, override, or auto-dispatched (Priority 1) |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      397[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | `override_reason_code` | If overridden, why (local knowledge, crew request, etc.) |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      398[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | `dispatcher_id` | Who made the final dispatch decision |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      399[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | `decision_timestamp` | When the optimizer produced the recommendation |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      400[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | `confirmation_timestamp` | When the dispatcher confirmed (or when auto-dispatch timeout expired) |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      401[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | `recommended_hospital` | Hospital recommendation at dispatch time |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      402[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      403[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Storage:** DynamoDB table with partition key `call_id` and sort key `decision_timestamp`. Enable DynamoDB point-in-time recovery. For immutability, use an IAM policy that denies `dynamodb:DeleteItem` and `dynamodb:UpdateItem` on the audit table for all principals except a break-glass administrative role. Alternatively, export audit records to S3 with Object Lock (Governance or Compliance mode) for tamper-evident long-term storage.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      404[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      405[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Retention:** Minimum 7 to 10 years. State EMS record retention requirements vary (California requires 7 years, New York requires 6 years from last patient contact, others vary). Default to 10 years to cover the most stringent state requirements plus a buffer for late-filed litigation. Use DynamoDB TTL for the active table combined with automated export to S3 Glacier Deep Archive after 12 months. The S3 bucket uses Object Lock in Compliance mode, meaning nobody (including root) can delete records before the retention period expires.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      406[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      407[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Access control:** The audit table is write-once from the dispatch Lambda and the dispatcher console. Read access is restricted to: medical director role, quality assurance team, legal/compliance team, and system administrators. All reads are logged via CloudTrail. Any bulk export requires a formal request through your compliance workflow.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      408[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
